\section{Related Work}
\label{sec:related}
%%===========================================================

\subsection{Temporal Modeling on Electronic Health Records}

Kraljevic \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref1} introduced Foresight,
a generative pretrained Transformer that models longitudinal
patient timelines from structured EHR data and clinical notes.
While demonstrating effective temporal trajectory learning at
scale, Foresight targets event forecasting rather than
workflow timing and is non-agentic.

Muyama \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref2} systematically reviewed
machine learning approaches for clinical pathway discovery,
covering process mining, clustering, and sequence mining.
The review underscores the gap between academic workflow
modeling and deployable real-time delay detection systems.

Ibing \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref3} applied supervised learning
with NLP-based phenotyping to identify diagnostic delays in
EHRs for Crohn's disease. The approach is retrospective and
static with no continuous monitoring component.

\subsection{ICU Outcome Prediction With Deep Learning}

Tang \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref4} proposed CNN-Transformer
and LSTM-Transformer hybrids for early sepsis prediction,
achieving advance warning several hours before onset. The
temporal methodology is relevant, but the target is clinical
outcome rather than workflow process timing.

Rasheed \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref5} applied LSTM-based deep
learning to sequential ICU chart events for readmission
prediction. The recurrent architecture is related to that of
ACWIS, but the work is outcome-centric with no workflow-timing
semantics.

Li \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref6} extended LSTM-based readmission
prediction using diagnostic embeddings on MIMIC-III. The work
is limited to single-center data and lacks workflow delay
modeling.

Xie \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref7} proposed diffusion-based
generative imputation for real-time ICU mortality prediction.
The system targets mortality outcomes and does not address
process-level delays.

\subsection{Agentic AI for Clinical Decision Support}

\"{O}\u{g}d\"{u}~\textit{et al.}~\cite{ref8} designed an
adaptive multi-agent LLM-based CDSS integrating biomedical
retrieval-augmented generation and web intelligence. The
agentic design is relevant, but the system operates on
question-answering tasks rather than EHR workflow timelines.

Karunanayake~\cite{ref10} provided a conceptual overview of
agentic AI for healthcare using multimodal LLMs with
chain-of-thought reasoning, lacking quantitative evaluation.

\subsection{Anomaly Detection in Time Series}

Hu \textit{et al.}~\cite{ref9} applied diffusion models to
unsupervised anomaly detection in multivariate time series.
Although adjacent to deviation detection, the evaluation uses
non-clinical datasets with no clinical explainability.

