is split at the patient level (\texttt{subject\_id}): 189,255
training rows (118,620 sequences), 38,051 validation rows
(23,293 sequences), and 39,671 test rows (24,656 sequences).
A mean-predictor baseline (predicting the training-set mean
for all test instances) yields a baseline MAE of 92.01\,min.

